<a name="buf-validate-FieldPath"></a>

### FieldPath

`FieldPath` provides a path to a nested protobuf field.

This message provides enough information to render a dotted field path even
without protobuf descriptors. It also provides enough information to resolve a
nested field through unknown wire data.

| Field    | Type                                               | Label    | Description                                                                                  |
| -------- | -------------------------------------------------- | -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| elements | [FieldPathElement](#buf-validate-FieldPathElement) | repeated | `elements` contains each element of the path, starting from the root and recursing downward. |

<a name="buf-validate-FieldPathElement"></a>

### FieldPathElement

`FieldPathElement` provides enough information to nest through a single protobuf
field.

If the selected field is a map or repeated field, the `subscript` value selects
a specific element from it. A path that refers to a value nested under a map key
or repeated field index will have a `subscript` value. The `field_type` field
allows unambiguous resolution of a field even if descriptors are not available.

| Field        | Type                                                                                    | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| ------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| field_number | [int32](#int32)                                                                         | optional | `field_number` is the field number this path element refers to.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| field_name   | [string](#string)                                                                       | optional | `field_name` contains the field name this path element refers to.<br/>This can be used to display a human-readable path even if the field number is unknown.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| field_type   | [google.protobuf.FieldDescriptorProto.Type](#google-protobuf-FieldDescriptorProto-Type) | optional | `field_type` specifies the type of this field. When using reflection, this value is not needed.<br/><br/>This value is provided to make it possible to traverse unknown fields through wire data.<br/>When traversing wire data, be mindful of both packed[1] and delimited[2] encoding schemes.<br/><br/>[1]: https://protobuf.dev/programming-guides/encoding/#packed<br/>[2]: https://protobuf.dev/programming-guides/encoding/#groups<br/><br/>N.B.: Although groups are deprecated, the corresponding delimited encoding scheme is not, and<br/>can be explicitly used in Protocol Buffers 2023 Edition. |
| key_type     | [google.protobuf.FieldDescriptorProto.Type](#google-protobuf-FieldDescriptorProto-Type) | optional | `key_type` specifies the map key type of this field. This value is useful when traversing<br/>unknown fields through wire data: specifically, it allows handling the differences between<br/>different integer encodings.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |
| value_type   | [google.protobuf.FieldDescriptorProto.Type](#google-protobuf-FieldDescriptorProto-Type) | optional | `value_type` specifies map value type of this field. This is useful if you want to display a<br/>value inside unknown fields through wire data.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| index        | [uint64](#uint64)                                                                       | optional | `index` specifies a 0-based index into a repeated field.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| bool_key     | [bool](#bool)                                                                           | optional | `bool_key` specifies a map key of type bool.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| int_key      | [int64](#int64)                                                                         | optional | `int_key` specifies a map key of type int32, int64, sint32, sint64, sfixed32 or sfixed64.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |
| uint_key     | [uint64](#uint64)                                                                       | optional | `uint_key` specifies a map key of type uint32, uint64, fixed32 or fixed64.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
| string_key   | [string](#string)                                                                       | optional | `string_key` specifies a map key of type string.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |

<a name="buf-validate-Fixed32Rules"></a>

If the field value doesn't meet the required conditions,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyFixed32 {<br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 5 [fixed32.gte]<br/> fixed32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).fixed32.gte = 5];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 5 and less than 10 [fixed32.gte_lt]<br/> fixed32 other_value = 2 [(buf.validate.field).fixed32 = { gte: 5, lt: 10 }];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 10 or less than 5 [fixed32.gte_lt_exclusive]<br/> fixed32 another_value = 3 [(buf.validate.field).fixed32 = { gte: 10, lt: 5 }];<br/>}<br/>` |
| in      | [fixed32](#fixed32) | repeated | `in` requires the field value to be equal to one of the specified values.<br/>If the field value isn't one of the specified values, an error message<br/>is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyFixed32 {<br/> // value must be in list [1, 2, 3]<br/> repeated fixed32 value = 1 (buf.validate.field).fixed32 = { in: [1, 2, 3] };<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
| not_in  | [fixed32](#fixed32) | repeated | `not_in` requires the field value to not be equal to any of the specified<br/>values. If the field value is one of the specified values, an error<br/>message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyFixed32 {<br/> // value must not be in list [1, 2, 3]<br/> repeated fixed32 value = 1 (buf.validate.field).fixed32 = { not_in: [1, 2, 3] };<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
| example | [fixed32](#fixed32) | repeated | `example` specifies values that the field may have. These values SHOULD<br/>conform to other constraints. `example` values will not impact validation<br/>but may be used as helpful guidance on how to populate the given field.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyFixed32 {<br/> fixed32 value = 1 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).fixed32.example = 1,<br/> (buf.validate.field).fixed32.example = 2<br/> ];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |

### Fixed64Rules

| in      | [fixed64](#fixed64) | repeated | `in` requires the field value to be equal to one of the specified values.<br/>If the field value isn't one of the specified values, an error message is<br/>generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyFixed64 {<br/> // value must be in list [1, 2, 3]<br/> repeated fixed64 value = 1 (buf.validate.field).fixed64 = { in: [1, 2, 3] };<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |

<a name="buf-validate-MapRules"></a>

### MapRules

MapRules describe the constraints applied to `map` values.

| Field     | Type                                               | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| --------- | -------------------------------------------------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| min_pairs | [uint64](#uint64)                                  | optional | Specifies the minimum number of key-value pairs allowed. If the field has<br/>fewer key-value pairs than specified, an error message is generated.<br/><br/>``proto<br/>message MyMap {<br/> // The field `value` must have at least 2 key-value pairs.<br/> map<string, string> value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).map.min_pairs = 2];<br/>}<br/>``                                                                                                         |
| max_pairs | [uint64](#uint64)                                  | optional | Specifies the maximum number of key-value pairs allowed. If the field has<br/>more key-value pairs than specified, an error message is generated.<br/><br/>``proto<br/>message MyMap {<br/> // The field `value` must have at most 3 key-value pairs.<br/> map<string, string> value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).map.max_pairs = 3];<br/>}<br/>``                                                                                                           |
| keys      | [FieldConstraints](#buf-validate-FieldConstraints) | optional | Specifies the constraints to be applied to each key in the field.<br/><br/>``proto<br/>message MyMap {<br/> // The keys in the field `value` must follow the specified constraints.<br/> map<string, string> value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).map.keys = {<br/> string: {<br/> min_len: 3<br/> max_len: 10<br/> }<br/> }];<br/>}<br/>``                                                                                                                    |
| values    | [FieldConstraints](#buf-validate-FieldConstraints) | optional | Specifies the constraints to be applied to the value of each key in the<br/>field. Message values will still have their validations evaluated unless<br/>skip is specified here.<br/><br/>``proto<br/>message MyMap {<br/> // The values in the field `value` must follow the specified constraints.<br/> map<string, string> value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).map.values = {<br/> string: {<br/> min_len: 5<br/> max_len: 20<br/> }<br/> }];<br/>}<br/>`` |

<a name="buf-validate-MessageConstraints"></a>

### MessageConstraints

MessageConstraints represents validation rules that are applied to the entire
message. It includes disabling options and a list of Constraint messages
representing Common Expression Language (CEL) validation rules.

| Field    | Type                                   | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| -------- | -------------------------------------- | -------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| disabled | [bool](#bool)                          | optional | `disabled` is a boolean flag that, when set to true, nullifies any validation rules for this message.<br/>This includes any fields within the message that would otherwise support validation.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyMessage {<br/> // validation will be bypassed for this message<br/> option (buf.validate.message).disabled = true;<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| cel      | [Constraint](#buf-validate-Constraint) | repeated | `cel` is a repeated field of type Constraint. Each Constraint specifies a validation rule to be applied to this message.<br/>These constraints are written in Common Expression Language (CEL) syntax. For more information on<br/>CEL, [see our documentation](https://github.com/bufbuild/protovalidate/blob/main/docs/cel.md).<br/><br/><br/>``proto<br/>message MyMessage {<br/> // The field `foo` must be greater than 42.<br/> option (buf.validate.message).cel = {<br/> id: "my_message.value",<br/> message: "value must be greater than 42",<br/> expression: "this.foo > 42",<br/> };<br/> optional int32 foo = 1;<br/>}<br/>`` |

<a name="buf-validate-OneofConstraints"></a>

### OneofConstraints

The `OneofConstraints` message type enables you to manage constraints for oneof
fields in your protobuf messages.

| Field    | Type          | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| -------- | ------------- | -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| required | [bool](#bool) | optional | If `required` is true, exactly one field of the oneof must be present. A<br/>validation error is returned if no fields in the oneof are present. The<br/>field itself may still be a default value; further constraints<br/>should be placed on the fields themselves to ensure they are valid values,<br/>such as `min_len` or `gt`.<br/><br/>``proto<br/>message MyMessage {<br/> oneof value {<br/> // Either `a` or `b` must be set. If `a` is set, it must also be<br/> // non-empty; whereas if `b` is set, it can still be an empty string.<br/> option (buf.validate.oneof).required = true;<br/> string a = 1 [(buf.validate.field).string.min_len = 1];<br/> string b = 2;<br/> }<br/>}<br/>`` |

<a name="buf-validate-PredefinedConstraints"></a>

### PredefinedConstraints

PredefinedConstraints are custom constraints that can be re-used with multiple
fields.

| Field | Type                                   | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| ----- | -------------------------------------- | -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| cel   | [Constraint](#buf-validate-Constraint) | repeated | `cel` is a repeated field used to represent a textual expression<br/>in the Common Expression Language (CEL) syntax. For more information on<br/>CEL, [see our documentation](https://github.com/bufbuild/protovalidate/blob/main/docs/cel.md).<br/><br/>``proto<br/>message MyMessage {<br/> // The field `value` must be greater than 42.<br/> optional int32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.predefined).cel = {<br/> id: "my_message.value",<br/> message: "value must be greater than 42",<br/> expression: "this > 42",<br/> }];<br/>}<br/>`` |

<a name="buf-validate-RepeatedRules"></a>

### RepeatedRules

RepeatedRules describe the constraints applied to `repeated` values.

| Field     | Type                                               | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| --------- | -------------------------------------------------- | -------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| min_items | [uint64](#uint64)                                  | optional | `min_items` requires that this field must contain at least the specified<br/>minimum number of items.<br/><br/>Note that `min_items = 1` is equivalent to setting a field as `required`.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyRepeated {<br/> // value must contain at least 2 items<br/> repeated string value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).repeated.min_items = 2];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                       |
| max_items | [uint64](#uint64)                                  | optional | `max_items` denotes that this field must not exceed a<br/>certain number of items as the upper limit. If the field contains more<br/>items than specified, an error message will be generated, requiring the<br/>field to maintain no more than the specified number of items.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyRepeated {<br/> // value must contain no more than 3 item(s)<br/> repeated string value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).repeated.max_items = 3];<br/>}<br/>`           |
| unique    | [bool](#bool)                                      | optional | `unique` indicates that all elements in this field must<br/>be unique. This constraint is strictly applicable to scalar and enum<br/>types, with message types not being supported.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyRepeated {<br/> // repeated value must contain unique items<br/> repeated string value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).repeated.unique = true];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                       |
| items     | [FieldConstraints](#buf-validate-FieldConstraints) | optional | `items` details the constraints to be applied to each item<br/>in the field. Even for repeated message fields, validation is executed<br/>against each item unless skip is explicitly specified.<br/><br/>``proto<br/>message MyRepeated {<br/> // The items in the field `value` must follow the specified constraints.<br/> repeated string value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).repeated.items = {<br/> string: {<br/> min_len: 3<br/> max_len: 10<br/> }<br/> }];<br/>}<br/>`` |

<a name="buf-validate-SFixed32Rules"></a>

### SFixed32Rules

SFixed32Rules describes the constraints applied to `fixed32` values.

| Field   | Type                  | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
| ------- | --------------------- | -------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| const   | [sfixed32](#sfixed32) | optional | `const` requires the field value to exactly match the specified value. If<br/>the field value doesn't match, an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MySFixed32 {<br/> // value must equal 42<br/> sfixed32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).sfixed32.const = 42];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| lt      | [sfixed32](#sfixed32) | optional | `lt` requires the field value to be less than the specified value (field <<br/>value). If the field value is equal to or greater than the specified value,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MySFixed32 {<br/> // value must be less than 10<br/> sfixed32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).sfixed32.lt = 10];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            |
| lte     | [sfixed32](#sfixed32) | optional | `lte` requires the field value to be less than or equal to the specified<br/>value (field <= value). If the field value is greater than the specified<br/>value, an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MySFixed32 {<br/> // value must be less than or equal to 10<br/> sfixed32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).sfixed32.lte = 10];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |
| gt      | [sfixed32](#sfixed32) | optional | `gt` requires the field value to be greater than the specified value<br/>(exclusive). If the value of `gt` is larger than a specified `lt` or<br/>`lte`, the range is reversed, and the field value must be outside the<br/>specified range. If the field value doesn't meet the required conditions,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MySFixed32 {<br/> // value must be greater than 5 [sfixed32.gt]<br/> sfixed32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).sfixed32.gt = 5];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than 5 and less than 10 [sfixed32.gt_lt]<br/> sfixed32 other_value = 2 [(buf.validate.field).sfixed32 = { gt: 5, lt: 10 }];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than 10 or less than 5 [sfixed32.gt_lt_exclusive]<br/> sfixed32 another_value = 3 [(buf.validate.field).sfixed32 = { gt: 10, lt: 5 }];<br/>}<br/>`                                                         |
| gte     | [sfixed32](#sfixed32) | optional | `gte` requires the field value to be greater than or equal to the specified<br/>value (exclusive). If the value of `gte` is larger than a specified `lt`<br/>or `lte`, the range is reversed, and the field value must be outside the<br/>specified range. If the field value doesn't meet the required conditions,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MySFixed32 {<br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 5 [sfixed32.gte]<br/> sfixed32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).sfixed32.gte = 5];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 5 and less than 10 [sfixed32.gte_lt]<br/> sfixed32 other_value = 2 [(buf.validate.field).sfixed32 = { gte: 5, lt: 10 }];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 10 or less than 5 [sfixed32.gte_lt_exclusive]<br/> sfixed32 another_value = 3 [(buf.validate.field).sfixed32 = { gte: 10, lt: 5 }];<br/>}<br/>` |
| in      | [sfixed32](#sfixed32) | repeated | `in` requires the field value to be equal to one of the specified values.<br/>If the field value isn't one of the specified values, an error message is<br/>generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MySFixed32 {<br/> // value must be in list [1, 2, 3]<br/> repeated sfixed32 value = 1 (buf.validate.field).sfixed32 = { in: [1, 2, 3] };<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |
| not_in  | [sfixed32](#sfixed32) | repeated | `not_in` requires the field value to not be equal to any of the specified<br/>values. If the field value is one of the specified values, an error<br/>message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MySFixed32 {<br/> // value must not be in list [1, 2, 3]<br/> repeated sfixed32 value = 1 (buf.validate.field).sfixed32 = { not_in: [1, 2, 3] };<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| example | [sfixed32](#sfixed32) | repeated | `example` specifies values that the field may have. These values SHOULD<br/>conform to other constraints. `example` values will not impact validation<br/>but may be used as helpful guidance on how to populate the given field.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MySFixed32 {<br/> sfixed32 value = 1 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).sfixed32.example = 1,<br/> (buf.validate.field).sfixed32.example = 2<br/> ];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |

<a name="buf-validate-StringRules"></a>

### StringRules

StringRules describes the constraints applied to `string` values These rules may
also be applied to the `google.protobuf.StringValue` Well-Known-Type.

| Field               | Type                                   | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |
| ------------------- | -------------------------------------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---- | ------ | ----------- | ----- | ------------------------------- | -------- | ------------------------------------------- | ----- | ----------------------- | --- | --- | ----- | ---------------------------- | --- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----- | ----------------------------- | --- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --- |
| const               | [string](#string)                      | optional | `const` requires the field value to exactly match the specified value. If<br/>the field value doesn't match, an error message is generated.<br/><br/>``proto<br/>message MyString {<br/> // value must equal `hello`<br/> string value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).string.const = "hello"];<br/>}<br/>``                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| len                 | [uint64](#uint64)                      | optional | `len` dictates that the field value must have the specified<br/>number of characters (Unicode code points), which may differ from the number<br/>of bytes in the string. If the field value does not meet the specified<br/>length, an error message will be generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyString {<br/> // value length must be 5 characters<br/> string value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).string.len = 5];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                     |
| min_len             | [uint64](#uint64)                      | optional | `min_len` specifies that the field value must have at least the specified<br/>number of characters (Unicode code points), which may differ from the number<br/>of bytes in the string. If the field value contains fewer characters, an error<br/>message will be generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyString {<br/> // value length must be at least 3 characters<br/> string value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).string.min_len = 3];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                   |
| max_len             | [uint64](#uint64)                      | optional | `max_len` specifies that the field value must have no more than the specified<br/>number of characters (Unicode code points), which may differ from the<br/>number of bytes in the string. If the field value contains more characters,<br/>an error message will be generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyString {<br/> // value length must be at most 10 characters<br/> string value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).string.max_len = 10];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                               |

### TimestampRules

TimestampRules describe the constraints applied exclusively to the

| const   | [google.protobuf.Timestamp](#google-protobuf-Timestamp) | optional | `const` dictates that this field, of the `google.protobuf.Timestamp` type, must exactly match the specified value. ### UInt32Rules

UInt32Rules describes the constraints applied to `uint32` values. These rules
may also be applied to the `google.protobuf.UInt32Value` Well-Known-Type.

| Field   | Type              | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| ------- | ----------------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| const   | [uint32](#uint32) | optional | `const` requires the field value to exactly match the specified value. If<br/>the field value doesn't match, an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt32 {<br/> // value must equal 42<br/> uint32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint32.const = 42];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
| lt      | [uint32](#uint32) | optional | `lt` requires the field value to be less than the specified value (field <<br/>value). If the field value is equal to or greater than the specified value,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt32 {<br/> // value must be less than 10<br/> uint32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint32.lt = 10];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| lte     | [uint32](#uint32) | optional | `lte` requires the field value to be less than or equal to the specified<br/>value (field <= value). If the field value is greater than the specified<br/>value, an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt32 {<br/> // value must be less than or equal to 10<br/> uint32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint32.lte = 10];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| gt      | [uint32](#uint32) | optional | `gt` requires the field value to be greater than the specified value<br/>(exclusive). If the value of `gt` is larger than a specified `lt` or<br/>`lte`, the range is reversed, and the field value must be outside the<br/>specified range. If the field value doesn't meet the required conditions,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt32 {<br/> // value must be greater than 5 [uint32.gt]<br/> uint32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint32.gt = 5];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than 5 and less than 10 [uint32.gt_lt]<br/> uint32 other_value = 2 [(buf.validate.field).uint32 = { gt: 5, lt: 10 }];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than 10 or less than 5 [uint32.gt_lt_exclusive]<br/> uint32 another_value = 3 [(buf.validate.field).uint32 = { gt: 10, lt: 5 }];<br/>}<br/>`                                                         |
| gte     | [uint32](#uint32) | optional | `gte` requires the field value to be greater than or equal to the specified<br/>value (exclusive). If the value of `gte` is larger than a specified `lt`<br/>or `lte`, the range is reversed, and the field value must be outside the<br/>specified range. If the field value doesn't meet the required conditions,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt32 {<br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 5 [uint32.gte]<br/> uint32 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint32.gte = 5];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 5 and less than 10 [uint32.gte_lt]<br/> uint32 other_value = 2 [(buf.validate.field).uint32 = { gte: 5, lt: 10 }];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 10 or less than 5 [uint32.gte_lt_exclusive]<br/> uint32 another_value = 3 [(buf.validate.field).uint32 = { gte: 10, lt: 5 }];<br/>}<br/>` |
| in      | [uint32](#uint32) | repeated | `in` requires the field value to be equal to one of the specified values.<br/>If the field value isn't one of the specified values, an error message is<br/>generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt32 {<br/> // value must be in list [1, 2, 3]<br/> repeated uint32 value = 1 (buf.validate.field).uint32 = { in: [1, 2, 3] };<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |
| not_in  | [uint32](#uint32) | repeated | `not_in` requires the field value to not be equal to any of the specified<br/>values. If the field value is one of the specified values, an error<br/>message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt32 {<br/> // value must not be in list [1, 2, 3]<br/> repeated uint32 value = 1 (buf.validate.field).uint32 = { not_in: [1, 2, 3] };<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| example | [uint32](#uint32) | repeated | `example` specifies values that the field may have. These values SHOULD<br/>conform to other constraints. `example` values will not impact validation<br/>but may be used as helpful guidance on how to populate the given field.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt32 {<br/> uint32 value = 1 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).uint32.example = 1,<br/> (buf.validate.field).uint32.example = 10<br/> ];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |

<a name="buf-validate-UInt64Rules"></a>

### UInt64Rules

UInt64Rules describes the constraints applied to `uint64` values. These rules
may also be applied to the `google.protobuf.UInt64Value` Well-Known-Type.

| Field   | Type              | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| ------- | ----------------- | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| const   | [uint64](#uint64) | optional | `const` requires the field value to exactly match the specified value. If<br/>the field value doesn't match, an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt64 {<br/> // value must equal 42<br/> uint64 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint64.const = 42];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
| lt      | [uint64](#uint64) | optional | `lt` requires the field value to be less than the specified value (field <<br/>value). If the field value is equal to or greater than the specified value,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt64 {<br/> // value must be less than 10<br/> uint64 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint64.lt = 10];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| lte     | [uint64](#uint64) | optional | `lte` requires the field value to be less than or equal to the specified<br/>value (field <= value). If the field value is greater than the specified<br/>value, an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt64 {<br/> // value must be less than or equal to 10<br/> uint64 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint64.lte = 10];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| gt      | [uint64](#uint64) | optional | `gt` requires the field value to be greater than the specified value<br/>(exclusive). If the value of `gt` is larger than a specified `lt` or<br/>`lte`, the range is reversed, and the field value must be outside the<br/>specified range. If the field value doesn't meet the required conditions,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt64 {<br/> // value must be greater than 5 [uint64.gt]<br/> uint64 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint64.gt = 5];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than 5 and less than 10 [uint64.gt_lt]<br/> uint64 other_value = 2 [(buf.validate.field).uint64 = { gt: 5, lt: 10 }];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than 10 or less than 5 [uint64.gt_lt_exclusive]<br/> uint64 another_value = 3 [(buf.validate.field).uint64 = { gt: 10, lt: 5 }];<br/>}<br/>`                                                         |
| gte     | [uint64](#uint64) | optional | `gte` requires the field value to be greater than or equal to the specified<br/>value (exclusive). If the value of `gte` is larger than a specified `lt`<br/>or `lte`, the range is reversed, and the field value must be outside the<br/>specified range. If the field value doesn't meet the required conditions,<br/>an error message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt64 {<br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 5 [uint64.gte]<br/> uint64 value = 1 [(buf.validate.field).uint64.gte = 5];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 5 and less than 10 [uint64.gte_lt]<br/> uint64 other_value = 2 [(buf.validate.field).uint64 = { gte: 5, lt: 10 }];<br/><br/> // value must be greater than or equal to 10 or less than 5 [uint64.gte_lt_exclusive]<br/> uint64 another_value = 3 [(buf.validate.field).uint64 = { gte: 10, lt: 5 }];<br/>}<br/>` |
| in      | [uint64](#uint64) | repeated | `in` requires the field value to be equal to one of the specified values.<br/>If the field value isn't one of the specified values, an error message is<br/>generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt64 {<br/> // value must be in list [1, 2, 3]<br/> repeated uint64 value = 1 (buf.validate.field).uint64 = { in: [1, 2, 3] };<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |
| not_in  | [uint64](#uint64) | repeated | `not_in` requires the field value to not be equal to any of the specified<br/>values. If the field value is one of the specified values, an error<br/>message is generated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt64 {<br/> // value must not be in list [1, 2, 3]<br/> repeated uint64 value = 1 (buf.validate.field).uint64 = { not_in: [1, 2, 3] };<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| example | [uint64](#uint64) | repeated | `example` specifies values that the field may have. These values SHOULD<br/>conform to other constraints. `example` values will not impact validation<br/>but may be used as helpful guidance on how to populate the given field.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message MyUInt64 {<br/> uint64 value = 1 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).uint64.example = 1,<br/> (buf.validate.field).uint64.example = -10<br/> ];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             |

<a name="buf-validate-Violation"></a>

### Violation

`Violation` represents a single instance where a validation rule, expressed as a
`Constraint`, was not met. It provides information about the field that caused
the violation, the specific constraint that wasn't fulfilled, and a
human-readable error message.

```json
{
  "fieldPath": "bar",
  "constraintId": "foo.bar",
  "message": "bar must be greater than 0"
}
```

| Field         | Type                                 | Label    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------ | -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| field         | [FieldPath](#buf-validate-FieldPath) | optional | `field` is a machine-readable path to the field that failed validation.<br/>This could be a nested field, in which case the path will include all the parent fields leading to the actual field that caused the violation.<br/><br/>For example, consider the following message:<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message Message {<br/> bool a = 1 [(buf.validate.field).required = true];<br/>}<br/>`<br/><br/>It could produce the following violation:<br/><br/>`textproto<br/>violation {<br/> field { element { field_number: 1, field_name: "a", field_type: 8 } }<br/> ...<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| rule          | [FieldPath](#buf-validate-FieldPath) | optional | `rule` is a machine-readable path that points to the specific constraint rule that failed validation.<br/>This will be a nested field starting from the FieldConstraints of the field that failed validation.<br/>For custom constraints, this will provide the path of the constraint, e.g. `cel[0]`.<br/><br/>For example, consider the following message:<br/><br/>`proto<br/>message Message {<br/> bool a = 1 [(buf.validate.field).required = true];<br/> bool b = 2 [(buf.validate.field).cel = {<br/> id: "custom_constraint",<br/> expression: "!this ? 'b must be true': ''"<br/> }]<br/>}<br/>`<br/><br/>It could produce the following violations:<br/><br/>`textproto<br/>violation {<br/> rule { element { field_number: 25, field_name: "required", field_type: 8 } }<br/> ...<br/>}<br/>violation {<br/> rule { element { field_number: 23, field_name: "cel", field_type: 11, index: 0 } }<br/> ...<br/>}<br/>` |
| field_path    | [string](#string)                    | optional | **Deprecated.** `field_path` is a human-readable identifier that points to the specific field that failed the validation.<br/>This could be a nested field, in which case the path will include all the parent fields leading to the actual field that caused the violation.<br/><br/>Deprecated: use the `field` instead.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
| constraint_id | [string](#string)                    | optional | `constraint_id` is the unique identifier of the `Constraint` that was not fulfilled.<br/>This is the same `id` that was specified in the `Constraint` message, allowing easy tracing of which rule was violated.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
| message       | [string](#string)                    | optional | `message` is a human-readable error message that describes the nature of the violation.<br/>This can be the default error message from the violated `Constraint`, or it can be a custom message that gives more context about the violation.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |
| for_key       | [bool](#bool)                        | optional | `for_key` indicates whether the violation was caused by a map key, rather than a value.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |

<a name="buf-validate-Violations"></a>

### Violations

`Violations` is a collection of `Violation` messages. This message type is
returned by protovalidate when a proto message fails to meet the requirements
set by the `Constraint` validation rules. Each individual violation is
represented by a `Violation` message.

| Field      | Type                                 | Label    | Description                                                                                                           |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------ | -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| violations | [Violation](#buf-validate-Violation) | repeated | `violations` is a repeated field that contains all the `Violation` messages corresponding to the violations detected. |

<!-- end messages -->

<a name="buf-validate-Ignore"></a>

### Ignore

Specifies how FieldConstraints.ignore behaves. See the documentation for
FieldConstraints.required for definitions of "populated" and "nullable".

| Name                    | Number | Description                                          |
| ----------------------- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| IGNORE_UNSPECIFIED      | 0      | Validation is only skipped if it's an unpopulated nullable fields.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>syntax="proto3";<br/><br/>message Request {<br/> // The uri rule applies to any value, including the empty string.<br/> string foo = 1 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).string.uri = true<br/> ];<br/><br/> // The uri rule only applies if the field is set, including if it's<br/> // set to the empty string.<br/> optional string bar = 2 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).string.uri = true<br/> ];<br/><br/> // The min_items rule always applies, even if the list is empty.<br/> repeated string baz = 3 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).repeated.min_items = 3<br/> ];<br/><br/> // The custom CEL rule applies only if the field is set, including if<br/> // it's the "zero" value of that message.<br/> SomeMessage quux = 4 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).cel = {/* ... */}<br/> ];<br/>}<br/>` | IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED   | 1      | Validation is skipped if the field is unpopulated. This rule is redundant<br/>if the field is already nullable. This value is equivalent behavior to the<br/>deprecated ignore_empty rule.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>syntax="proto3<br/><br/>message Request {<br/> // The uri rule applies only if the value is not the empty string.<br/> string foo = 1 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).string.uri = true,<br/> (buf.validate.field).ignore = IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED<br/> ];<br/><br/> // IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED is equivalent to IGNORE_UNSPECIFIED in this<br/> // case: the uri rule only applies if the field is set, including if<br/> // it's set to the empty string.<br/> optional string bar = 2 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).string.uri = true,<br/> (buf.validate.field).ignore = IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED<br/> ];<br/><br/> // The min_items rule only applies if the list has at least one item.<br/> repeated string baz = 3 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).repeated.min_items = 3,<br/> (buf.validate.field).ignore = IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED<br/> ];<br/><br/> // IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED is equivalent to IGNORE_UNSPECIFIED in this<br/> // case: the custom CEL rule applies only if the field is set, including<br/> // if it's the "zero" value of that message.<br/> SomeMessage quux = 4 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).cel = {/* ... */},<br/> (buf.validate.field).ignore = IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED<br/> ];<br/>}<br/>`                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |
| IGNORE_IF_DEFAULT_VALUE | 2      | Validation is skipped if the field is unpopulated or if it is a nullable<br/>field populated with its default value. For messages, the<br/>default is a non-null message with all its fields unpopulated.<br/><br/>`proto<br/>syntax="proto3<br/><br/>message Request {<br/> // IGNORE_IF_DEFAULT_VALUE is equivalent to IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED in<br/> // this case; the uri rule applies only if the value is not the empty<br/> // string.<br/> string foo = 1 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).string.uri = true,<br/> (buf.validate.field).ignore = IGNORE_IF_DEFAULT_VALUE<br/> ];<br/><br/> // The uri rule only applies if the field is set to a value other than<br/> // the empty string.<br/> optional string bar = 2 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).string.uri = true,<br/> (buf.validate.field).ignore = IGNORE_IF_DEFAULT_VALUE<br/> ];<br/><br/> // IGNORE_IF_DEFAULT_VALUE is equivalent to IGNORE_IF_UNPOPULATED in<br/> // this case; the min_items rule only applies if the list has at least<br/> // one item.<br/> repeated string baz = 3 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).repeated.min_items = 3,<br/> (buf.validate.field).ignore = IGNORE_IF_DEFAULT_VALUE<br/> ];<br/><br/> // The custom CEL rule only applies if the field is set to a value other<br/> // than an empty message (i.e., fields are unpopulated).<br/> SomeMessage quux = 4 [<br/> (buf.validate.field).cel = {/* ... */},<br/> (buf.validate.field).ignore = IGNORE_IF_DEFAULT_VALUE<br/> ];<br/>}<br/>`<br/><br/>This rule is affected by proto2 custom default values:<br/><br/>```proto<br/>syntax="proto2";<br/><br/>message Request {<br/> // The gt rule only applies if the field is set and it's value is not<br/> the default (i.e., not -42). | IGNORE_ALWAYS           | 3      | The validation rules of this field will be skipped and not evaluated. <a name="ory-keto-relation_tuples-v1alpha2-WriteService"></a>

### WriteService

The write service to create and delete Access Control Lists.

This service is part of the
[write-APIs](../concepts/25_api-overview.mdx#write-apis).
